rComments: Lectures aren't super exciting, but they are 100% thorough. She goes through every step of derivations which is really helpful. She's super approachable, never makes you feel dumb. Very knowledgeable but humble and chilled out. Tests and problem sets are 100% fair. No tricks. With modest effort you can do well. + Her accent is cute! Wonderful lady

Horrible professor. Has an accent (Austrian?) and just reads off the slides. I stopped going to her lectures after the first two because she didn't add anything of value and the slides were online. If you're taking CHM135 avoid her!

Horrible at explaining concepts.... scratch that, doesn't explain anything at all. Just reads off the slides I stopped going to her lectures after the first two because she didn't say anything that was worth writing down and the slides were all online anyways. Has an accent (Austrian?) and gives far-fetched irrelevant examples.

This professor rushes through lectures and does not give students chance to attempt practice problems. Her explanations of concepts were mediocre at best. Thankfully, CHM135 isn't a difficult course, otherwise I would be in deep trouble if I had her for a more advanced course.
Not a good prof. Very difficult to understand her due to her accent.
She is simply amazing! The best physical chemistry prof I have ever had.
